headline: Umicore - Transparency notification by JP Morgan Asset Management Holdings Inc.
summary: Transparency notification by JP Morgan Asset Management Holdings Inc. In accordance with article 14, § 1 of the law of 2 May 2007 on the disclosure of major holdings, Umicore was recently notified by JP Morgan Asset Management Holdings Inc. that it has crossed the legal threshold of 3% for the direct voting rights upwards on 16 September 2025. The total holding of direct voting rights and equivalent financial instruments of JP Asset Management Holdings Inc. stands at 3.01% on 16 September 2025.

headline: Oracle Looks to Raise $15 Billion From Corporate Bond Sale
summary: The technology giant — which has nearly doubled in value this year — is selling the debt in as many as seven parts, including a rare 40-year bond, people familiar with the matter said, asking not to be identified discussing private details.  Initial price discussions for that portion of the deal are in the area of 1.65 percentage point above similarly dated Treasuries.  The deal comes as Oracle begins to fulfill massive cloud infrastructure deals with customers like OpenAI and Meta Platforms Inc., which are boosting the company’s expenses.

headline: Analysis-Financial firms to feel outsized impact from Trump's H-1B overhaul
summary: NEW YORK (Reuters) -The Trump administration's overhaul of the H-1B system could have an outsized impact on the finance industry, which could face hiring challenges following the imposition of the new $100,000 fee.  Financial firms are among the largest users of H-1B visas, employment-based visas awarded by an annual lottery, although their usage is dwarfed by tech companies.  One analyst said it will be harder for banks than for tech companies to bear the increased cost.
